nFor confidence levels, I'm considering whether infrastructure could expose issues. The cron parser likely operates as a pure function, so Unit testing at 0.95 confidence is appropriate with 0.05 for System. The missed-run detector might call datetime.now() internally, but that's mockable at the Unit level—keeping Unit at 0.90 with 0.05 System and 0.05 Integration. The overlap detector appears to compare two schedules directly rather than querying a job database, so Unit dominates at 0.75, with Integration at 0.20 and System at 0.05. Timezone handling depends on tzdata availability, but using the real tzlib during Unit tests covers this without needing OS-level validation.\n\nFor the last behavior, if the detector accepts last-run time as a parameter rather than fetching it from a database, Unit testing suffices at 0.85 confidence, with Integration at 0.10 and System at 0.05. Each distribution sums to 1.0 across all five behaviors.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13492,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13492},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b306585-783c-4005-bd05-adff82dd9656","uuid":"662e88bc-367c-454b-b91a-9d28b768a6a1"}
